<br>
Just hit 30 - a friend tells me about the Ire's at Collorary - he warns me about the chain casting sprites - I find the Ires, I see a sprite, I shoot it, my shot rate turns out to be faster than its cast rate, I own it, I stop worrying about the sprites.  15 minutes later, I am jumped by one and am summarily ownt.<br>
<br>
I say, ah, ok - I'll tackle some mist wraiths, then - they are easy.  I spend an hour so getting a bub, I get sloppy, I get jumped by a yellow right after a fight, I am ownt.<br>
<br>
I check out a web post somewhere that says &quot;fight the Siabra Wayslayers in Lough Gur&quot; - I go there, I find some mobs called Gurrite Wayslayers in more or less the right place, I figure thats who he meant - I start fighting, one calls for help and I don't notice, I am ownt.<br>
<br>
I get a rez.  I see a blue.  I decide I will take the blue even though I still have rez sickness.   I will never again try to fight solo with rez sickness.  I am ownt.<br>
<br>
I log for a bit.  I decide to go back at the Wayslayers.  I am much more careful this time, having learned my lesson.  All through the day, I fight hard and well, yellows and blues chain fall to my singing bow.  A high level party is fighting pookhas down the road from me, so I don't fear the horsies.  I almost have my bub back (I never did manage to find my grave <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
Night falls, I see a LOT of running humanoids.  I think it is a guild - I con one - d'oh!  a pack of purple Siabras RUNNING DOWN THE ROAD LIKE THEY OWN IT!  I /yell look out!  Siabras coming! but not knowing if the pookha hunters heard me, I sprint to them and say &quot;big pack of Siabras coming&quot;.  No immediate panic from them, I figure they know what's what - I hang out to watch.  The Siabras arrive, pookha hunters are getting ownt BIG time.  I use whats left of my endurance to sprint away, and hide by the water.  Turns out, the water edge is a lot safer by day than by night - I am quickly ownt (Dullahan, btw).<br>
<br>
hee hee.  what a day ....<br>
<br>
