<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Just yesterday, while in the Frontier, I kept getting the message, &quot;You can't stealth this close to an enemy!&quot;  I spun my camera around, and saw a Frost Horse (or whatever they are) near me.  I move about 15 feet away from it, and try to restealth.  Again I get the message.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Damn, this horse must have Detect Hidden,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I think.  I move another five feet away and remash the button.  Again I get the message.  I step 5 feet forward and out of the Horse's range, and suddenly a shadow appears blinks into and out of existance behind me.  For a second, I think it is lag, then I realize that this shadow is twice my height, and carrying two daggers in a fighting stance.<br>
<br>
I did a /laugh, then hit the sprint button for the Frontier gates.  You'd have thought that some purple Assassin willing to spend all that time following me would have used /stick to stay on me when I moved. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><i>"People will believe any lie you give them; whether it is because they wish it to be true, or fear it to be true." -<b>Wizard's First Rule</i></b>
